          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_InsertBudgetGroupsPrerequisite",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage budget group data for a specified fiscal year. It performs operations on two tables: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Preload.BudgetGroup",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Preload.BudgetGroupByFY",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure inserts new budget groups into these tables based on the input list of IDs and handles the deletion of existing records under certain conditions. It also ensures that a specific budget group (ID 62) is always present for the given fiscal year."
        }
      ]
    },
